news.title: Shree Cements posts profit of Rs 701.85 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: The company had posted a net profit of Rs 281.83 crore in the October-December period a year ago, according to a regulatory filing, its revenue from operations grew 21.5 per cent to Rs 5,223.18 crore during the quarter under review. It was at Rs 4,299.26 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding fiscal.

news.title: Ambuja Cement posts net profit of Rs 1,089.55 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: The company had clocked a net profit of Rs 487.88 crore in the October-December quarter a year ago, its consolidated revenue from operations increased 2.8 per cent to Rs 8,128.80 crore during the quarter under review. It was Rs 7,906.74 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates posts net loss of Rs 476 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Total income declined to Rs 1,558.58 crore during the October-December period of this fiscal year from Rs 1,933.11 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Lucknow development body sells commercial plots worth over Rs 675 crore
news.para: Besides commercial plots designated for group housing, schools, health centers/nursing homes, and mixed-use plots, were sold out, LDA chairman Roshan Jacob distributed certificates to the allottees at a function held on Tuesday and assured them of issuance of allotment letters within 15 days.

news.title: Noida authority sets Rs 120 crore water dues target, 10 housing societies make up 80% of them
news.para: The Noida Authority has raised Rs 94.5 crore in revenue from water bills, while the dues amount to Rs 94.6 crore. Officials said they have pasted notices at all the societies concerned and are attempting to collect the remaining water bills from the defaulters.

news.title: Dhar land scam: ED attaches movable & immovable property
news.para: “The action of provisionally attaching movable/immovable properties of the main mastermind of the land scam Sudhir Ratnakar Peter Das and others have been attached under the provision of Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002,”

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body scores big on second day of auctions
news.para: The Makarba plot, a 3,799 sq metre residential parcel, saw bids go from a base rate of Rs 35,000 per sq m to Rs 82,000, a premium of Rs 32,000. Similarly, the 2,623 sq m commercial plot in Vatva drew wide interest and ended up fetching Rs 38,000 per sq m, Rs 3,000 above the base rate.

news.title: Over 850 get house allotment letter in Kanpur
news.para: Though the awas scheme comprises 1,104 flats, 864 are complete and allotted to beneficiaries through lottery. The department had received 18,514 applications from aspirants and 4,852 of them were found eligible. Remaining 240 flats are under construction and would be allotted later through lottery.

news.title: Delhi: MCD extends last date for geotagging properties to February 29
news.para: Delhi Mayor Shelly Oberoi on December 7 said the AAP-led Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) had set the ball rolling for creating a "proper database" of property tax records using cutting-edge technology.

news.title: Mumbai: Block E & G of Bandra-Kurla Complex to get a global FSI of four
news.para: According to a senior member of a high power committee set up to recommend premium on FSI, new developments and redevelopment of old buildings were considerations for proposing a global FSI of 4 for Blocks E and G of BKC.

news.title: MahaRERA issues notices to 41 unregistered plot projects
news.para: MahaRERA officials were checking properties in response to complaints from homebuyers regarding delays in projects in rural areas, when they found that developers of many plotted areas had sold units without registration or QR code mandatory for all projects above 500sqm.

news.title: Structural audit dues: Town planner to serve notice to builders, RWAs in Gurugram
news.para: The district administration will also hold a meeting with developers and RWAs to settle the issues which are halting and delaying the process, adding to the concerns of families living in the highrise buildings.

news.title: Pune: Too few builders opt for treated water in construction over quality concerns
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) has objected to the use of potable water and said it would take strict measures, such as giving stop-work notices if developers were found using drinking water for construction purposes.

news.title: Order to liquidate China Evergrande is just one step in fixing China's debt crisis
news.para: Evergrande owes $340 billion to its creditors. Experts say it's unclear if Monday's order will be enforced in mainland China, where the company and 90% of its assets are based.

news.title: Mumbai police's EOW arrests Supreme Constructions' director in cheating case
news.para: Lalit Tekchandani was brought to the EOW office in south Mumbai on Tuesday evening and placed under arrest after questioning, he said.

news.title: Barclays Bank, K Raheja Corp ink Rs 306-crore lease deal for office in Mumbai
news.para: The financial major's India arm will be effectively paying a lease of nearly Rs 306 crores throughout the lease term for a total 64,000 sq ft office space on 32nd and 33rd floors of the office tower Altimus developed by realty developer K Raheja Corp’s subsidiary Whispering Heights Real Estate.

news.title: Grasim Industries Rs 4,000-crore rights issue over subscribed
news.para: The company has received a cumulative bid for nearly 4.34 crore shares as against 2.21 crore shares offered by the Aditya Birla Group firm, according to an exchange filing.

news.title: Keystone Realtors posts net profit of Rs 29.88 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Keystone Realtors' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 533.33 crore in Q3 FY24 as against Rs 135.55 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit falls 7% to Rs 11 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Kamdhenu's total income fell to Rs 157.45 crore from Rs 183.17 crore in the year-ago quarter. However, it trimmed its expenses to Rs 142.43 crore from Rs 167.06 crore a year ago.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance targets $600 million India IPO: Sources
news.para: Private equity group Blackstone acquired Aadhar for about $300 million in 2019 as it bet on growing demand for affordable housing and financing in India.
